{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d1024f2e-3f43-43a5-895c-c5258964f952","content":"In .NET MAUI, use the **lifecycle events API** in `MauiProgram.cs` (or your app builder setup):\n\n```csharp\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android => android\n        .OnPause(activity =>\n        {\n            // runs when the Android activity is paused\n        })\n        .OnStop(activity =>\n        {\n            // runs when the Android activity is stopped\n        }));\n#endif\n\n#if IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n        .DidEnterBackground(app =>\n        {\n            // runs when the iOS app enters background\n        }));\n#endif\n});\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- Add `using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;` at the top.\n- Platform guards (`#if ANDROID` / `#if IOS`) ensure the code only compiles for the target platform.\n- Other events are available too — `OnResume`, `WillEnterForeground`, `OnCreate`, etc.\n- This is configured on the `MauiAppBuilder`, so it runs before any page loads.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a45dd663-4c21-4c0b-8a35-28473ef02b2e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI — specifically Android's `OnPause`/`OnStop` and iOS's `DidEnterBackground`. This is a general knowledge question, not a code task.","outputTokens":350,"requestId":"F3DC:D1352:1DCF123:219DD8A:69E819FE"},"id":"119d1a56-6a8d-421c-ae5f-197ba9895864","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:44:54.058Z","parentId":"ba4c3d69-e51f-433d-9571-379d513919e3"}
